name: Walmart Supercenter
address: Walmart Supercenter, 5900 Littlerock Rd SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, United States

detailed_reviews.review_text: Friendly staff and clean restrooms..Almost always have what I need . Also they price match..Roll back dem prices fellas$$. $$

Very good service with home grocery delivery. Makes it easier for me to shop online and have groceries delivered to my front door. I am elderly and have physical impairments. Very handy for me not to have to go to store to do my shopping.
One of more clean and organized walmarts I have been too. I actually enjoy shopping here.

Great store large selection I shop here consistently every pay day as well I am a spark delivery driver,I have been to a few different locations to deliver and I do have to say that the tumwater location has some of the hardest grocery pick up workers I have seen even when they are backed up or low staffed they give all of the employees available to keep the orders flowing as fast as they can.

This walmart is great, the store is always clean and I always receive great service. There are 3 employees that are always helpful, Austin, Joel, and Tristan. They always greet me when I see them and are ready to help whenever Ive asked. Thanks guys, great job.
I love Walmart and their prices. They are seldom out of products. Walmart is where I buy my dog fresh pet select. Great place to shop, the employees are very helpful.
The reason for shopping there is price,but they also have some good pastries in the bakery

I ve stopped by the Walmart Supercenter on Littlerock Road SW in Tumwater while staying at the La Quinta Inn & Suites while working in the area. This way I can pick up any items that I might need or want as I stay the week here. The parking lot is large with plenty of easy to find spots. Everyone here seems super friendly and helpful. When I went recently there was a lot of selection for items but it sounds like lately some things are flying off of the shelves.

Went to Tumwater Walmart today .They open at 7AM .I can tell you if you want help finding something which I did, got there  at 7:30 AM on a Saturday you have plenty of help and not many other shoppers their .Very large ,clean ,bright and well stocked store .
Had everything needed & employees were helpful.

Wanted to shout out LACEY in the vision center. She was so kind and sweet and went out of her way to fix my broken sunglasses, even last minute at the end of the night. She literally went above and beyond for no other reason than kindness :) She got me patched up super quick and even thanked ME for my patience?! You are awesome Lacey, thank you again :D

Unlike  Safeway,  Walmart, both  corporate and  Tumwater Store, ACTUALLY CARE what customers complain about.  After complaining about milk which was unbagged and was placed directly on the ground,  now Walmart doesnt do it. On the contrary,  Safeway, both  corporate and Stores at  Canyon Rd and  Harrison Ave, have never corrected wrongs -  putting an unbagged milk directly on the ground, and selling  1 or 2 days old fresh salad packs and bakery items. To both Safeway corporate and both Stores, I  complained numerous times about their ignoring food safety.  Im switching to Walmart.
Its like every Walmart I have ever seen to in my life, they had sunhats for cheap. I got a cool one.

Wondering service in the optical center. Brandon is very nice, extremely knowledgeable and very patient. I got what I needed for less than what frames alone cost in another store. Great service * Great price*
I frequently shop at this location and like the people here. Very helpful
Great place to find everything you need. All the employees were their best and helped me find were things where.
Clean, well organized, normal shoppers, not too crowded for a Monday afternoon. In/out in 30 minutes.
Liquor store and gun range.  It is very well put together.  It is well worth using.
These guys have it all why go to all these other stores when you can wrap it all up in one fatal swoop thats how I look at it
A wide range of items of all kinds make it an ideal place to shopping. The prices are also comparatively good.
Its got the regular stuff. I enjoy every aisle being the same. Makes it easier to look around. The number of fast checkout is ample and accessible almost every time.

Yeah, they have the good ramen back again, wish they had pork flavor. Im so happy that I dont have to go find it somewhere else. Thank you Walmart. Im disappointed in the fact that you cant buy Christmas food items with food Stamps at Walmart. I have to go to other places to get the santa, snowman, Elf on the shelf candies. I use to get my family a new mug each Christmas to have cocoa in while we read the night before Christmas. You cant buy them any more. The little jelly gift sets, my Grandma loved getting, you cant get them, and the 12 days of Christmas barbecue sauce, or hot sauce, you cant get anymore. So for my familys favorite food Christmas gifts Im going to shop elsewhere. Off to Big Lots by Capital Mall, they have lots to pick from, and great deals too.
Great place for most needs including the supplies for the off-grid solar communities.

Christmas eve morning. Walmart was up and running! The General manager was in the floor stocking shelves next to hourly employees. The staff was energetic and seemed to be filled with the holiday spirit.
I mean its wamart. Got pretty much all the walmart stuff lol

If there is a good Walmart, this one is it. Selection and service is second to none. Even though this location is always busy, their associates are always working hard and keep the floor stocked as best as possible. This location has a great beer selection and is always early with seasonal merchandise. This location doesnt have an auto service center.

Went to get car ramps and got the last pair I thought they would be easier than the jack but found out I need guiding onto the ramps after that got worked out my big Impala was parked on them for almost 24 hours advertised to support 12,000lbs definitely true....
Cleaner than the lacey store but the lines are still too long
Not a problem when getting groceries at all
ALL WAL-MARTS ARE THE DEFINITION OF WHITE TRASH, BUT THIS ONE IN OREGON SUCCESSFULLY PORTRAYS ALL WHITE STEREOTYPES IN ONE-STOP SHOPPING
Very convenient with good customer service
My go to store for my wild bird food. Nice selection of foods.

Since my last post where I mentioned that on opening of the store there would be just one cashier line open and long lines would build up, management has implemented improvements. After speaking to one of the store managers (a nice speaking lady) more cashier are now available once the line builds. So it is refreshing when your concerns are heard and positively responded too.
The pharmacy was efficient and friendly. There was no wait to check out with a cashier because everyone was in line to self check out.
Walmart is always a good place to go get the things you need, from clothes to food for dinner.

Hardly ever shop at Walmart, unless it is an emergency and they are the only business that has an item (since they are nearby). However, this particular location isnt bad. Just wish they would use cashiers again, it seems checkout is now self-service.
Good selection and well stocked. Employees were doing their thing and stocking. Clean bathrooms.
Good store with everything you can need. Unfortunately, with inflation for prices have gone significantly up. At least here, you can keep costs under control. Also, very close to my home.

Sick with the latest COVID crud , my husband and I put in a huge Walmart pick up order online.  All was per usual for our pick up but I did comment to my husband that I thought there would be more bags.  So we head home ( an hour away ) and get home unpack the groceries and find we are missing all the protein , all the meats we ordered were not there. I called the help line on the app and talked to someone that was rude and utterly unhelpful and refused to get me her supervisor. Finally frustrated I hung up on her and called my store. The Tumwater WA store. I was told the pick up team was busy And they would call me back. I waited an hour and called the store when I got to talk to Lucas right away. He was amazing. Very sweet and was able to find my meats. I drove back to the store and called the number and Michael ( I think he said his name was ) can hustling right out and loaded it up for me. He was also really nice and easy.  Maybe it was just me figuring this would be another battle but the local store was so helpful and just plain nice.  You guys are being an amazing job and this sick old lady sure appreciated these two gentleman. I really hope this get back to their bosses and they are at the very least acknowledged for being super hero s today.  Thank you so much.

I mean, its Walmart. What else is there to say? Although, I did manage to find small packs of pocket composition notebooks that I havent been able to find anywhere else lately with some help from staff.
It was snowing hard so had a hard time seeing where the curbside pickup was. The loading was fast and the employee was very courteous.
We pick up groceries every week. Karen is oftentimes delivering the groceries to our car. She is so kind and nice every single time. She is great.
Went to the optometrist at Walmart to have lens put back in glasses and tighten frames. Quick service, professional, friendly staff. I will go back.
Always great prices and a clean store, most of the time!

Found everything we were looking for plus great clearance racks found shoes and long sleeves mens shirts for amazing prices! It was very clean and the staff at self check out were very nice and Johnny on the spot to help when one item had no tag. They are awesome there!
So many choices... Personally love the Garden section
I can always find what Im looking for.
This store is set up nice well stocked. Clean friendly staff. But with everyone less the pet food isnt always fully stocked but check back they get stuff every day.
Had a problem with my receipt,  upper managment too care of it right away. Very unexpected,  Thank You So Much.

OMG, BEST EXPERIENCE OUT OF MY 32 YEARS AT WAL-MART I EVER HAD. MY CASHIER MADE MY DAY. SO GENUINE AND SHE SHOWED NE AN ACT OF KINDNESS THAT MEANT A KOT TO ME. SO I WANNA SHOUT OUT TO OPERATOR# 000094!!! I DIDNT EVEN LOOK TO SEE HER NAME & RECEIPT ONLY HAS OP#. BUT LOVELY WOMAN WHO WORKS AT TUMWATER, WA WAL-MART. THANK YOU!! YOU HAVE A SPECIAL ORA AND SINCERITY ABOUT YOU THAT MAKES YOU ONE OF THEM ONES. HOPE LIFE BRINGS YOU NOTHING BUT BLESSINGS AND THAT WAL-MART GIVES YOU A BIG FAT RAISE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I can always count on finding what I need. This last visit, I really really appreciated staff wearing face masks, saw ferocious cleaning going on and I dont mind the slight wait to enter when its a busy day at Walmart. Thank you for making it safe. I hope employees are being taken care of - they pour their hearts out for us.

I had to do pick-up from online. I had to be there late last night to pick it up. The girl that helped me was so kind and helpful. It is rare to find people in retail that go out of their way to be helpful, and kind - - especially late in the evening. She even put my purchase in a box for me so my kids wouldn t see their Christmas gift. She then reopened it and put the tag on the outside of the box so that I wouldn t have issues when leaving.

Havent been inside the store in 2 years.  I started using the pickup in Aug 2019...and I am a BIG fan (before Covid).  Theyre online images and descriptions are the BEST ones.  Ive tried every store in our town for curbside pickup and have stopped.  The employees who load your car are the best, and I hope Walmart raises them up while finding ways to keep our prices from skyrocketing.
Fast and friendly. I have been using the pickup service for over a year. Being handicapped  it is the BEST way for me to get everything I  need.
It was really clean and organized. The staff was nice and helpful. Cleanest Walmart Ive ever been to.

I love that everything is set up neatly, merchandise is easy to find and always kept picked up. The employees are quick to help when asked, and are always respectful and kind. Definitely recommend if youre looking for great prices for quality items, and a welcoming friendly environment.

Better than any of my local stores in Sacramento, Calif!! My husband and I stopped off her on our way to Shelton for Thanksgiving. The first thing I noticed was how pleasant the greeter was, like she actually was happy to see us. I also appreciated that she let me put my husbands seizure dog in the cart (under the basket on a blanket) and didnt make him walk. After the 15 hour drive our normally relaxed service dog was as out of sorts as we were. It really did mean a lot. Everything in the store was easy to locate, it was a bit crazy to see how well layed out they had their store in preparation for black Friday. The arrows on the ground were a kick! Self check out was easy and there was no wait. The lady who checked our receipt was nice and let me wait to the side while my husband got the car, as it was pouring and we were not prepared. Were actually planning on moving to Washington in the next year and this seems like a very friendly community. Thanks!
All the Employees very helpful and Friendly. The Women in the Deli are always happy too wait on you. They never act too busy, like other stores.

The online shopping experience was great. Its very easy to order online the products you want , pay with your credit card. Then you pick a time when you want to pick up your stuff, or have it delivered to your home. Much less stress than actually going into the store.

Quick shopping experience and Staff were either sticking or cleaning. All staff(i experienced and saw) were masked and socially distant, situation permitting.  Staff were friendly coming into and leaving the store
Always intersting stuff to buy at a reasonable price
Halloween stuff half price

My girlfriend and I got there a hr and a half before closing, when it got down to 45 mins before closing about a handful of lost prevention people were all over the place and this one particular guy was extremely obvious and I caught him staring at me and then trying to hide down a isle peeking and so i called him out because I was just simply shopping and I felt like I was being stalked  or something. And he continued to keep doing wouldnt stop even after I called him out.
J5 ran in and got two things
Everyone is usually really friendly, can get busy quite quickly. My only gripe is that I walked in without a mask (forgot I wasnt wearing one) and no one told me or asked me to put one on
Great location surrounded by many other stores.

The line into the store moves quickly oh, masks required. They had the cart sanitized so you can just grab the one you want and go. This time we had to shop for shoes for my boys and we were able to find what were looking for a fairly quickly. All employees were very polite and happy to help if I had a question. I was able to find some vegan shredded cheese and a new brand that I had heard about that hadnt tried so I was very excited for that, I think it was Follow your Heart vegan cheese also CHAO. Were trying to reduce plastic so it was a little disappointing that the sweet potatoes and certain other vegetables and fruits were wrapped in Plastics or bagged. However they also had the Dyia cheese gluten-free pizzas which I have been wanting to try, I was also very happy about that. A pretty good variety of different things at the store we also have meat eaters in our family. Husband was able to get the shrimp he needed, lunch meat and regular Dairy like milk and cheeses no problem. Lots of good sales and prices in general the few things that we werent able to get I was able to get at a store near our a house as Walmart is a bit far from my home.

The pharmacy here is the best in Thurston county. The doctor sends the prescription to them from his office and I can head there right after the appointment and they will have it ready! The workers at this location are also the best Walmart workers in the state.
I like that you can get your groceries, clothes, and medication. Or plants all at the same place... You dont have to go to 3 different stores.. And the people are very nice and helpful....
Clean facility,very nice friendly people, they had the ammunition I wanted at the price I wanted... Im happy.
I love how organized everything is at this store. Although, with how many employees you see on the floor. Cleaning or stocking I feel like they try to avoid customers when you have a question.
River helped me find VEGAN Best Foods mayonnaise, Yay!! Im allergic to eggs and so was very grateful for his help. Very nice employee, thank you for carrying egg-free products.
I know nothing about video games and the gentleman went above and beyond to help me even though he was already really busy. Ill definitely be back! And my was happy as well. Thanks Ben!
They had what I wanted and a quick checkout

Awesome! My checker was supper friendly and the ladies at guest services. Who I saw  an hour later because I had lost/dropped my phone and they were holding it for me! My favorite was Bud at the door ohhh hes a hoot made my night! P.s. if your in the mood for strawberries they are amazing right now!

The Walmart Superstore is unbelievably massive, so before you go there take some aspirin let it kick in and start one side and then work your way up and down each of the isles, (oh wear some comfortable shoes) dont go when youre hungry and, just take your time there, and remember try not to TOUCH everything and then put it back Please, Thank you for your patience, we are trying not spread the Covid-19 virus around if we can help it. Again Thanks for everything youve done to keep us safer. Merry Christmas Everyone.

Employees that were stocking the shelves were very nice by getting things for me if their pallets were in the way and pick up a 40 bottles of water and. Put it in my cart for me. I am 60 yrs. old and its hard for me. And my granddaughter showed her slime she made to a few of them and they were very nice and smiled and talked back to her. But the cashier . Was not very friendly at all.Its like they are afraid to talk to us. They just rush us thru. Deli was not friendly at all.!!!!. The stocker on floor get a  A+  from me.
Pharmacy staff is friendly and efficient. Selection throughout the store is great, prices are good. Store is clean. We use self checkout which is quick and easy.

U need it, they most likely have it, except for Big Red soft drinks. They dont carry it anymore. Which is one reason they dont get five stars! They are open 24 hours also which is great! Only problem is if u shop at night, they all look at u like ur gonna steal something.. as if thieves are the only ones awake after 11pm.grrr... They are no longer open 24 hours. My review is really one star! But I had to make sure the maximum number of people see this! New Info! CAUTION RECOMMENDED! If you want to catch COVID this is the place to shop! This has been since the mandate was lifted. I happen to know one of their employees (who shall remain nameless). Contracted Covid, tested positive, was home for 3 days. Had no more leave- still testing positive. Was told by management at Walmart that company policy states they come to work or risk being terminated! Even tho they were testing positive for the Corona Virus!! So  with as many people as their are shopping at Walmart. It s safe to say, they are the biggest reason The Corona Virus is still a problem!! They are a national chain!! This is Walmart s standard practice!! Spreading the Virus!!!

Had a blast shopping tonight. Weather kept a lot of people indoors. I appreciate the Wal-Mart employees that came into work during this winter storm. I got great customer support from at least 3 employees tonight who all, quickly assisted me in locating items and navigating through the store. I was in and out faster than I anticipated with their help. The store was clean and well staffed. I especially liked the fact that the floor mats at the entrance were maintained and not left soaking wet. They were mostly dry when I walked into the store. Highly reccomend this Wal-Mart store to anybody looking for great service.

I love Sharis!  When youre in the mood for a home cooked meal at a reasonable price this is where I go!  Tonight I had a med. rare sirloin broccoli crowns and a loaded baked potatoe.  My meal was seasoned and cooked to perfection!
I like this store, always clean and nice people.

Walmart is doing well. All employees are wearing masks and theres rarely a line. Bring something to wipe the cart with, though. They are doing well with controlling how many customers are in the store at any one time. Most of the customers arent wearing masks, though.

Couldnt say enough about there toilet. It cupped my bunger pretty tight and I didnt have the painfully pre-warmed seat. I also noticed that the mens bathroom did not smell like cigarette butts and urine like most public boys bathrooms. #mypooplikeswalmart

Ok, its Walmart, you have to manage your expectations   When Ive been here, Ive had consistently good shopping experiences. This is mainly because somehow it never seems crowded, if I didnt have three kids age five and under with me, it would actually be almost peaceful, which with the aforementioned littles I crave on an ongoing basis! Maybe its just that its so big, maybe its that I havent been there during peak times, Im not sure. I do my grocery shopping at Fred Meyer and it always seems like a madhouse, no matter when I go, and this is quiet and pleasant by comparison.
As someone who has been in many walmarts, this one is the most beautiful one if ever been to. Its clean and well stocked. The associates I talked to were very kind and helpful.
Took the family shopping. Staff were friendly. Bathroom was clean. Store was tidy. Found all items easily. Checkout was fairly quick. This store had a receipt checking policy.

Walmart out did their selves on this rare occasion,I dropped my phone in a swimming pool while hanging with my son at the pool ,they sol me a phone and service that started the day I bought it,and the provider I was using couldnt even compare in price and my service still had 20@days on it upon falling in the water.

It is sad to see product left in the wrong places by shoppers. The employees are very helpful and great listeners. The Gorilla Snot hair product I purchased the other day is just fabulous and it is also fun to say!

After having a bad experience at a local optometry facility, I read the reviews of a number of eyewar places and Walmart  Tumwater rated very high. I went in and was totally blown away with everything from customer service to disinfecting everything. Bottom line - totally impressed.
Ordered online, picked up @ Pick Up Lot, quick and pleasant service.
Great deals great prices and very helpful people I purchased a TV last night and I didnt know what I was doing and the person helping me was very good I love Walmart

This is the nicer Walmart in comparison to Lacey. Nothing ever seems out of stock. Have done curbside pick up for groceries during the toilet paper crisis. And had a great experience with that as well.

Uumm wheres the car lot in this thing! Such a huge store you can get lost in for hours.  Super good food products and Walmart prices on stuff and things.  Good amount of registers that are actually open hold the phone I thought I was in a parallel universe! Good job you...good job
Its one of the Big Walmarts. Cool as heck and has just about anything youd think. Great selections of everything and lots of friendly staff when i went.

Clean store, Good prices, Theres nothing bad to say about this store.  In my opinion the Customer service department is lacking help.  I waited 40 minutes in line to buy stamps. Thats me being dumb and waiting when I could of went to Safeway.
Well stocked and safe (except for the folks, who wont wear masks, which was every customer in the store). Line up outside to be let in so the store is kept at a minimum of people inside. I like that.
The people are friendly and returns are a breeze. The lines arent long and there self check out is also quick. The fastest is checking out in garden. I always get help right away if I need it.
My favorite Walmart to go too. I live out in Rochester, and I prefer driving to this one than going to the one in Centralia. Its much quieter and isnt crammed pack full of people.
I locked my keys in my car and the staff was very nice and helpful! They even let us put our ice cream in the freezer while we waited. Amazing customer service.
